<HEADLINE>
<P>
REBUILDING THE COLISEUM FOR THE L.A. RAIDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The mayor of Los Angeles has formed a committee of businessmen and others to 
keep professional football in the city. 
</P>
<P>
The other California cities have gotten the bidding for a sports franchise into 
the $200-million range, and the end is apparently not in sight. The enlightened 
civil leaders seem hellbent on providing an area for a handful of athletes 
while muddling about on what steps to take to provide adequate housing for the 
working poor. Let the games begin. 
</P>
<P>
RUSS MARLETT 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
