<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXPANDING L.A. COUNTY BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I must respectfully take issue with some of the points raised in your 
editorial. 
</P>
<P>
The Times has long supported expansion of the five-member Board of Supervisors 
and election of a county executive; so have Supervisor Kenneth Hahn and I, and 
we signed the ballot arguments for proposed county charter amendments to 
accomplish that in 1976 and 1978. 
</P>
<P>
The Times has called upon the board to settle the case out of court and spare 
county taxpayers the time and expense of a protracted trial; so have Supervisor 
Hahn and myself. 
</P>
<P>
We have made every effort to persuade a majority of our colleagues to this 
position. In this light, I believe it is both unfair and inaccurate to ignore a 
significant difference of opinion on policy, strategy and tactics among the 
board's membership and lump us all together. 
</P>
<P>
EDMUND D. EDELMAN 
</P>
<P>
Supervisor, Third District 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles County 
</P>
</TEXT>
