<HEADLINE>
<P>
REBUILDING THE COLISEUM FOR THE L.A. RAIDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I root for the Raiders. George Blanda and Dave Casper, and then Jim Plunkett 
and Coach Tom Flores and Marcus Allen taught me to root for the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
But when it comes to a test between Al Davis and the Los Angeles Coliseum, I 
forget all about the Raiders. The Los Angeles Coliseum is the next greatest 
thing in California to the Golden Gate Bridge. 
</P>
<P>
I rarely advocate lynching; it is quite uncivilized. Tearing down the Coliseum 
would be as uncivilized as lynching. May the people considering it get the 
point. 
</P>
<P>
GILBERT S. BAHN 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
