<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SON, 18, HELD IN FATAL SHOOTING OF FATHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 18-year-old West Covina man shot and killed his father with a semiautomatic 
rifle after the older man tried to break up his son's party early Friday, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Royce Labuguen was arrested at his house and booked on suspicion of murder and 
held without bail, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Labuguen allegedly shot his father three times after the man asked him to break 
up a party with five friends about 3 a.m., Sgt. Richard Nelson said. Alexis 
Labuguen, 39, was shot in the chest, the right arm and the left leg in his 
son's bedroom at the Miranda Street house. 
</P>
