<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE DECLINE OF DAN RATHER'S RATINGS AFTER THE BUSH INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rick Du Brow's Jan. 6 article on the decline of Dan Rather's ratings after his 
1988 interview with then-candidate George Bush didn't quite tell it all: Rather 
and his team of Bush haters such as Lesley Stahl and Bob Schieffer have carried 
on the vendetta. 
</P>
<P>
When Gen. Manuel Noriega was captured, Rather spent the last 10 minutes of his 
show in a memorial to the dead in Panama, American and local, and a discussion 
of all the bad things that occurred in Panama with not one statement of the 
good things that came out of the U.S. action. This was the most biased, 
dishonest type of reporting, and Rather was not criticized in the print medium 
about doing it. 
</P>
<P>
GEOFFREY POST, Santa Maria 
</P>
</TEXT>
