<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: ESCONDIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange Glen Elementary School in Escondido has become the county's first to win 
a new computer system under a program sponsored by the Vons grocery company. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Glen received an Apple IIe Color System Friday after parents and friends 
of the school collected cash register tape receipts totaling $175,000. 
</P>
<P>
Any of the county's 490 schools can compete for six different Apple systems by 
collecting the receipts. A minimum of $65,000 is needed for the least expensive 
system. Orange Glen already has raised an additional $100,000 in receipts as 
part of its goal toward winning six systems before the program ends in mid-May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
