<HEADLINE>
<P>
17-YEAR-OLD STABBED IN BURBANK GANG DISPUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old Burbank boy was in extremely critical condition Friday after he 
was stabbed several times during a gang dispute, Burbank police said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, whose name was not released, was found collapsed in the street in the 
1600 block of Edison Road at 4:30 p.m. Thursday, Sgt. Don Goldberg said. 
</P>
<P>
He was taken to St. Joseph Medical Center, where he underwent surgery to remove 
one lung and was in the intensive care unit Friday, Goldberg said. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses told investigators that the teen-ager had been stabbed during a 
street fight and staggered about a block before collapsing, Goldberg said. 
</P>
<P>
"It is definitely a gang-related stabbing," Goldberg said. "It appears the 
young man got into a verbal altercation with several members from an opposing 
gang and then was stabbed several times in the back." 
</P>
<P>
Goldberg said detectives had no suspects, and the identity of the assailants' 
gang was not known. 
</P>
