OFFICIALS HUDDLE WITH DAVIS ON POSSIBLE MOVE BY RAIDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oakland authorities, led by Mayor Lionel Wilson, met for two hours with Los 
Angeles Raiders owner Al Davis on Friday to discuss that city's bid for the 
football team to return to its former home in Oakland. Afterward, Davis called 
it "a good meeting" but gave no indication when he might decide between 
competing bids from Oakland, Sacramento and Los Angeles -- all vying to be the 
future home for the Raiders. 
</P>
