Savings Bond Sales Up 3%: Sales of U.S. savings bonds totaled $593 million in 
December, bringing to $7.64 billion the total amount of sales for the year, the 
Treasury Department reported. The 3% increase of sales over calendar 1988 also 
increased the amount of bonds held by the public to a record $117.7 billion. 
Savings bonds currently earn interest at a rate of 6.98% when held five years 
or longer. 
