<TEXT>
<P>
Ansett World Aviation Services of Australia has ordered $110 million worth of 
jet engines from Pratt &amp; Whitney to power as many as 12 Airbus aircraft, 
Pratt &amp; Whitney said. 
</P>
<P>
Ansett ordered PW4000 engines for six A300-600R Airbus twin jets, a total of 14 
engines including spares, and took options on 12 more engines to power another 
six planes, said Pratt &amp; Whitney, a unit of United Technologies Corp. 
