<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAY DIED OF NATURAL CAUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The death of Cal State Northridge football player Tommie Gray last month was 
due to natural causes, the Los Angeles County coroner's office disclosed 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Gray, 21, collapsed and died of a heart attack Dec. 15 while visiting with 
friends near the pool at University Park Apartments in Northridge. A spokesman 
for the coroner's office said that Gray died of conjunctive cardiomyopathy, the 
result of an enlarged heart. 
</P>
<P>
Gray's family has a history of heart disease. The player's father reportedly 
died of a heart attack at age 27. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-3, 235-pound Gray, of Modesto, started at nose tackle for the 
Matadors. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
