<P>
SCHOOL BOARD TOLD CLASSROOMS NEEDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID F. BURKE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city school district will need additional classrooms to handle growing 
enrollment by September, according to a report to the school board this week. 
</P>
<P>
New portable classrooms may be needed at El Cerrito, Las Positas, Sierra Vista, 
Imperial and Washington schools, the report said. Replacement buildings may 
also be installed at Las Lomas Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
Schools Supt. Rich Hermann was directed to investigate alternate methods for 
funding a purchase of new buildings. 
</P>
<P>
Although the district has a special reserve fund containing $1.3 million, board 
members are reluctant to draw money needed for new portables from that source, 
board members said. DAVID F. BURKE 
