<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CORONA DEL MAR; 
</P>
<P>
BAYSIDE DRIVE SEWER LINE WORK TO BEGIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLIE HERZOG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A contractor was selected this week for the Bayside Drive phases of a sewer 
line project to serve planned homes on Newport Coast, the unincorporated Irvine 
Co. land between Corona del Mar and Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
McGrand &amp; Associates of Calimesa, Calif., was awarded the $2-million 
contract for the installation of sewer lines along scenic Bayside Drive from 
Coast Highway in Newport Beach to Marguerite Avenue in Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Work will begin in about six weeks, said Corinne Clawson, County Sanitation 
Districts spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
The final phase of the project, to be installed through the Corona del Mar 
business district on East Coast Highway to the south city limits, will be under 
construction after Pelican Hill Road is completed next year, according to a 
resolution passed earlier that prohibits downtown upheaval before the bypass 
road is in place, said Councilman Phil Sansone. 
</P>
<P>
Sansone said sections of Bayside Drive, a popular alternate route for 
commuters, will be restricted or closed during the construction. Traffic is 
expected to worsen on Coast Highway until summer when construction is scheduled 
for completion. LESLIE HERZOG 
</P>
</TEXT>
