<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRITISH ROYAL BALLET CANCELS TOUR OF U.S. THAT INCLUDED O.C. STOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS PASLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Royal Ballet of Great Britain has dropped plans to tour the United States 
in July and August, saying its unable to raise enough money, according to a 
story in the Friday edition of the New York Times. 
</P>
<P>
The tour, announced by the company in August, was to have included the Orange 
County Performing Arts Center as the last of three stops. The tour would have 
begun in New York and moved to Washington. 
</P>
<P>
The Royal Ballet last visited Southern California in 1979. CHRIS PASLES 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ROYAL BALLET OF GREAT BRITAIN; BALLET 
</P>
